➜Drinking water makes people happy? US latest research: People who drink more than six cups of water a day are more optimistic and energetic
http://www.sohu.com/a/439033286_162758	21509
<p>When asked what is the key to happiness, many people's answer may be love or family. However, the studyfinds website reported on the 12th that a new survey of 2,000 Americans showed that the real answer may be to stay hydrated. The survey found that people who stay properly hydrated tend to be happier, more successful, and more energetic.</p>
<p>Among the respondents who drink at least six glasses of water a day, 41% most agree with the view that "I am happy". Among those surveyed who drank less than a glass of water a day on average, only 12% held this view.</p>
<p>The survey also showed that among the people who drink more than six cups of water a day, 40% of the respondents think they are positive and optimistic, while the proportion of people who drink less than one cup of water a day is only 10%.</p>
<p>According to reports, hydration also has a great impact on rest and energy recovery. People who drink a lot of water every day (over six cups) wake up and feel tired on average 2.59 times a week, while those who drink very little water wake up and feel tired on average 3.14 times a week. In addition, people who are well hydrated are more likely to succeed and are the least likely to be late for work.</p>
<p>[责任编辑: 张舟 ] </p>
